summary: This document is an email chain from January 11, 2021, among federal prosecutors and law enforcement personnel from the New York Office Child Exploitation and Human Trafficking Task Force. They are coordinating schedules to interview a newly identified potential statutory victim in the Maxwell case. The emails discuss availability for the interview over the following two weeks.

persons.name: Assistant United States Attorney
persons.context: The sender of the initial email, coordinating the victim interview schedule and identifying a new potential statutory victim in the Maxwell case.

events.title: Scheduling of Victim Interview
events.description: Federal prosecutors and task force members coordinate their availability to interview a newly identified potential statutory victim in the Maxwell case.

locations: New York Office Child Exploitation and Human Trafficking Task Force
keyFacts: The email chain is from January 2021, indicating ongoing investigative activity in the Maxwell case at that time.
A new potential statutory victim has been identified in the Maxwell case, prompting the scheduling of an interview.
One participant mentions driving to and from Florida for victim interviews in the Maxwell case the following week.
The correspondence involves the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York and the Child Exploitation and Human Trafficking Task Force.
The document shows procedural coordination between federal prosecutors and law enforcement for victim interviews.
